<HEADLINE>
HEY LADY!  
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
  ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by clients of ``HIGH STYLE AND MORE.''
Nonsubscribers can use this article only by special arrangement.
For purchase information, see end of text. 
 &HT;    
 (Three color slides are available.) 
 From WWD 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
 &HT;    Remember the dress-for-success look from the '70s? Well, many
elements of that period are back _ with a ladylike slant.
 &HT;    This season's perfectly pulled-together ensembles pay homage to
the days when being treated like a lady depended on dressing like
one.
 &HT;    Tie-front blouses, bright halter dresses and tailored pants have
a discreet yet sexy charm _ for day or night.
 &HT;    
 c.2000 Fairchild Publications 
