<P>
   INTERNET FAITHFUL FLOCK TO JIM CLARK, PROPHET OF PROFIT, by Tish
Williams
</P>
<P>
   Women with tear-stained faces passed their babies forward,
entrusting them to the hands of strangers. Jim Clark gazed at each
and waved his hand in blessing. Palm by palm, Internet start-up
ideas were brought to the outstretched arms of the holy man.
</P>
<P>
   As celebratory M80s were fired off outside the high-tech
cathedral, the sweat-soaked, tightly packed start-up pilgrims
surged toward the stage. They were here to see the man who
communicates directly with the alternately cruel and benevolent god
of Internet success.
</P>
<P>
   The billionaire didn't disappoint the faithful.
