</P>
<P>
   CONCORDE-CRASH _ GONESSE, France _ Investigators have fully
extracted the data from the ``black box'' recorders aboard the Air
France Concorde that crashed
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday, and have begun analyzing cockpit conversations and
engine readings made during the supersonic aircraft's doomed
two-minute flight, the French government said Thursday. The
government agency that investigates aviation accidents said
</P>
<P>
   it was unclear how soon the information contained on the flight
data and cockpit voice records would yield clues about what caused
the crash that killed 113 when
</P>
<P>
   the Concorde slammed into a small hotel near Paris. A memorial
service has been scheduled here in Gonesse for Thursday. Meanwhile,
a French aviation engineer
</P>
<P>
   who serves as an official adviser to French courts told La Croix
newspaper that evidence and observations suggest that a turbine
disc in the jet engine may have
</P>
<P>
   failed. Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Expected to move by 4 p.m. (ET) on the NYT Wire.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-JERUSALEM _ JERUSALEM _ When low-level negotiators can't
settle a dispute, they usually ``bump it upstairs'' for a decision.
When it comes to the
</P>
<P>
   Holy City of Jerusalem, maybe The Man upstairs should settle the
dispute. An Israeli academic, who consults with negotiators in the
peace talks between Israel and the Palestinians, suggests they
break their deadlock by giving God sovereignty over the holiest
parts of the city. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Location, Atlanta; Category, International; Subcategory,
Other.
</P>
<P>
   MOVED on the NYT Wire in both International and Lifestyle
categories.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-MURDER-0728 _ MEXICO CITY _ When Juan Jesus Posadas
Ocampo, the Cardinal of Guadalajara, was machine-gunned to death in
his car outside the city's airport seven years ago, distraught
Mexicans wondered if their country was headed for hellish
Colombia-style violence. On Thursday, authorities here reveal the
conclusions of a years-long investigation into the shocking murder
of the Cardinal, who was riddled with bullets while wearing his
vestments and crucifix. An initial theory was that the Cardinal was
a mistaken target caught in the crossfire of two vicious
international drug-trafficking gangs, one of which is
</P>
<P>
   still on the FBI's most wanted list. The current Cardinal of
Guadalajara, a sharp critic of Mexican authorities' efforts to
investigate the crime, has said he fears the cardinal was murdered
in a conspiracy. (Ferriss).
</P>
