<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Voter apathy generated by a feeling
that there wasn't much difference between the two presidential
tickets may not be a problem in the current election. By picking a
doctrinaire conservative as his running mate, George W. Bush has
dropped his cloak of moderation to identify with the right wing.
Vice President Al Gore is now considering whether to pick a running
mate from his party's left wing. This is what elections are all
about _ choosing between different philosophies of governing. By
MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
