<DOCNO> NYT20000727.0156 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-27 16:21 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4766 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e BC-TV-KATHIELEE-TEX     07-27 0274
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-KATHIELEE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GOODBYE, KATHIE LEE. ENOUGH SAID
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEN PARISH PERKINS 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Kathie Lee Gifford exits ``Live With Regis &AMP; Kathie Lee'' on
Friday, and not a moment too soon. Letters, e-mails and phone calls
have piled up since her last visit to this space, where I tried,
unsuccessfully it now appears, to make the point that morning
television personalities are governed by the same rules of any
social setting.
</P>
<P>
   Either you like to hang out with these folks or you don't,
turning the channel to someone else.
</P>
<P>
   I've long turned away from Gifford, whose banter with Regis
Philbin was a delight, but who as an individual has no standout
qualities I consider worth a television talk show.
</P>
<P>
   Ever since that column, Gifford fans have been after my
firstborn and have questioned my sanity and even my patriotism,
which I still don't get.
</P>
<P>
   Most vocal was a retiree who in the past few years has become a
morning TV junkie, an expert on Katie Couric and Matt Lauer, the
brother and sister Osmonds, and any cable nature series showing a
mother eating its young.
</P>
<P>
   She wholeheartedly stands behind the adage that if you have
nothing nice to say about someone ``shut up,'' which suits me fine,
particularly in this case.
</P>
<P>
   That said, Gifford, 46, signs off Friday from ``Live With Regis
&AMP; Kathie Lee.'' Sob or celebrate.
</P>
<P>
   (Ken Parish Perkins is TV critic for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. You can call him at (817) 390-7862, or e-mail:
kpperkins(at)star-telegram.com. Visit the Star-Telegram's online
services on the World Wide Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
