<P>
   Getting There From New York
</P>
<P>
   BY AIR: Continental, (800) 525-0280, has three nonstop flights
daily from Newark. The least expensive fare is $251, which requires
a 21-day advance purchase and a Saturday stay over. The last-minute
fare is $580.50 each way. A 14-day advance purchase can range from
$293 to $562 round trip. U.S. Airways, (800) 428-4322, goes to
Nashville from La Guardia Airport at 6:45 a.m. and 12:55 p.m. and
makes stops but no change of plane. The early flight makes two
stops, in Raleigh for 40 minutes and in Charlotte for less than an
hour. The latter flight stops in Charlotte for 45 minutes. The
least expensive fare requires a 21-day advance purchase and a
Saturday stay over at $246. The 14-day fare is $288. Last-minute
fare is $578 each way. Other airlines that go to Nashville, with
connections, include TWA, (800) 221-2000; American Airlines, (800)
433-7300; and Delta Airlines, (800) 221-1212.
</P>
