   JOHNSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Developments at the recently concluded G-8 summit
summon to mind thoughts of Jim Smiley and his frog, Daniel Webster.
Such an association may seem like a bit of stretch to some. But
others may find the comparison not overly farfetched, because the
richer nations of the world pledged at the summit to help the
poorest make a great leap forward. That's what Smiley helped Daniel
Webster do. By CECIL JOHNSON. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary
category. &QL; 
