</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ ATLANTA _ Test driving a station wagon is not
normally something that would make my heart skip a beat. But I was
driving through the scenic rolling mountains of southern France.
The vehicle was Volvo's V70 wagon. My drive partner was He
Drove/She Drove's Paul Lienert. Paul tossed me the keys and assumed
the duties of navigator. (Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TESTDRIVE _ ATLANTA _ If you think the Chevrolet Corvette Z06
isn't one hot item, consider this: Somewhere between its
manufacture and initial drives by magazine writers at the proving
grounds in Michigan and Atlanta, the brilliant red car lost the
``Z06'' emblem off its right front fender _ and chip marks
indicated it didn't just fall off. (DeVault, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
