 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story CAMPIGN-NADER
(p) by Glen Johnson, which moved Monday, will wish to use the
following corrective.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A Boston Globe article about Ralph Nader, the Green Party
nominee for president, incorrectly described Nader's stance on
trade. Nader is a critic of free-trade agreements which he believes
are economically misguided and insufficiently safeguard worker
rights.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
