<HEADER>
A4862 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e BC-KATHIE-LEE0728-COX     07-27 0364
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KATHIE-LEE0728-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Celebrating the Kathie Lee in all of us
 &HT;    By Diane Holloway
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ We've been in denial. We've tried to pretend it
couldn't happen. But it's finally here, after months of
teeth-grinding buildup: Kathie Lee Gifford's last day on ``LIVE
with Regis &AMP; Kathie Lee.''
</P>
<P>
   From the moment she debuted with Reege on the eponymous morning
chat show, she garnered if not respect, at least attention. From
her mind-bending hairdos and attire to her mind-melting chatter,
we'd never known anyone quite like her.
</P>
<P>
   Her crimes were many, her fine points few: Remember when her
Wal-Mart clothing line was revealed to be manufactured in Honduran
sweatshops? Remember when husband Frank Gifford was caught in
compromising photos with a flight attendant? (On the heels of
months of smug churn from Kathie Lee about what a devoted husband
Frank was?) And how she vowed to keep her children out of the
public eye _ only to immediately appear with son Cody on the covers
of numerous women's magazines (and star with him in a made-for-TV
movie!)?
</P>
<P>
   Well, Kathie Lee may be leaving Regis, but that doesn't mean she
has to leave us! Here are a few ways to cultivate the Kathie Lee in
you in everything you do:
</P>
<P>
   _ Add ``ie'' and ``Lee'' to your name, practice your big wink
and screeching ``REEGE''!
</P>
<P>
   _Stock up on all the fine Kathie Lee products: books, CD,
clothing, the soon-to-debut home furnishings line.
</P>
<P>
   _ Boycott ``LIVE'' until Kathie Lee agrees to come back and end
our national nightmare!
</P>
<P>
   _ Kick off every day with 20 minutes of inane chat with
coworkers. Include at least one appallingly personal detail.
</P>
<P>
   _ Take a Carnival Cruise, don a Kathie Lee sw strawberry blonde
at every visit.
</P>
<P>
   _ Talk incessantly about your inner child, Cody.
</P>
<P>
   _ Proclaim shock at revelation that Third World laborers exist.
</P>
<P>
   _ It's time to start rehearsing your repertoire of cabaret
songs.
</P>
<P>
   _ Make the ultimate sacrifice: Have an affair with Frank.
</P>
<P>
   On second thought, we agree with the New York Post: So go,
already!
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-27-00 1758EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
