(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By WENDELL BARNHOUSE 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ Ricky Williams is using reverse logic. The
way he sees it, a pass-oriented offense will help the Red Raiders'
running game.
</P>
<P>
   New Texas Tech coach Mike Leach, the architect of pass-happy
offenses at Oklahoma and Kentucky, will have the Red Raiders
throwing the ball 60 to 70 percent of the time.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think the new offense will benefit me in varied ways,'' the
Texas Tech senior running back said yesterday at the league's
annual preseason media meeting. ``I think I'll be able to make
longer runs, have less carries and the field will be more open for
me because the defense will be spread out.''
</P>
<P>
   In 1998, Williams rushed for 1,582 yards and averaged nearly 30
carries a game. In two seasons at Tech, he has 28 receptions. The
carries are expected to go down while the receptions should
increase.
</P>
<P>
   Leach has rarely had a running back such as Williams, whose 1999
season was derailed by a knee injury, to complement his passing
game.
</P>
<P>
   ``Having a runner like Ricky, someone capable of gaining 1,000
yards, will be huge for this offense,'' said Leach, who makes his
head coaching debut Aug. 26 against New Mexico in Lubbock. ``We'll
get Ricky the ball as much as possible, but instead of handing it
to him so much we'll throw it to him.''
</P>
<P>
   ``My whole career it's been Ricky can just run the football and
nothing else,'' Williams, 5-foot-9 and 195 pounds, said. ``I've
wanted to be an in-between back, somebody who can run and catch.''
</P>
<P>
   He plans on doing a lot of both. His goal is to total 1,000
yards rushing and 1,000 yards receiving.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wouldn't count Ricky Williams out on anything,'' Leach said.
 &QL; 
Briefly
</P>
<P>
   Arrowhead Stadium officials estimate they have sold 35,000 of
their 60,000 ticket allotment for the Big 12 championship game Dec.
2 in Kansas City. Tickets are being sold to only Kansas City Chiefs
season ticket holders, but general public ticket sales will start
sometime in September.
</P>
<P>
   A media poll for the Big 12 Conference race predicts the
following order of finish: North _ Nebraska, Kansas State,
Colorado, Kansas, Iowa State and Missouri. South _ Texas, Oklahoma,
Texas A&AMP;M, Texas Tech, Oklahoma State and Baylor. Nebraska was
picked to defeat Texas in the Big 12 title game.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
