(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JEFF CAPLAN 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Stars are taking baby steps toward bringing defenseman Dave
Manson back into the fold by slightly increasing their offer to the
33-year-old unrestricted free agent.
</P>
<P>
   ``They have made an offer that David and I will consider,''
Manson's agent Don Meehan said yesterday. Meehan said he will talk
with Manson today and then get back to the Stars.
</P>
<P>
   Before Manson became an unrestricted free agent July 1, he
rejected the Stars' offer of $500,000 per season for one or two
seasons. Manson was paid $1.65 million last season and is looking
for a team where he could fit in as a top-four defenseman. Manson
would play as a third-pair defenseman with the Stars.
\Nsubheds:Network schedule ESPN and ESPN2 released their NHL
television schedules yesterday for the 2000-01 season. The networks
will carry 124 regular-season games, 27 on ESPN and 97 on ESPN2.
The Stars will make a total of 16 appearances, beginning Oct. 4 at
Reunion Arena against Colorado on an exclusive ESPN telecast.
</P>
<P>
   The Stars visit the New Jersey Devils for an ESPN telecast Dec.
20, and ESPN2 will televise the Devils' only trip to Texas on Jan.
24. The Stars play eight times on ESPN, including another matchup
against Colorado (March 11), two games against St. Louis (Feb. 11,
March 25), and a meeting against Detroit (Feb. 18).
\Nsubheds:Rookie camp The Stars are scheduled to hold a rookie camp
Aug. 10-20 at Dr Pepper StarCenter in Irving. Most of the club's
young talent from it's minor-league affiliate, the Michigan
K-Wings, will be in attendance, plus the Stars' 2000 first-round
draft pick Steve Ott. \Nsubheds:Pro scout hired The Stars named
Paul McIntosh as the club's new professional scout yesterday.
McIntosh most recently served as vice president of hockey
operations (1998-2000) as well as general manager (1996-97) for the
London Knights of the Ontario Hockey League. In 1998, McIntosh was
named the OHL and Canadian Hockey League Executive of the Year.
\Ntagtop:Jeff Caplan, (817) 390-7760
\Ntagbottom:jcaplan\Nstar-telegram.com
